Cape Town - A fire broke out, reportedly at a furniture factory, in Epping Industria on Tuesday morning. The cause of the fire is as yet unknown. Fire and Rescue's Theo Layne said eight fire engines were part of the detail responding to the incident. "The City's Fire and Rescue Service responded to Duiker Avenue, Epping Industrial Area just after 9am this morning. Currently we have a total of 12 firefighting vehicles on the scene including eight fire engines and two water tankers as well as a rescue vehicle on the scene. No injuries have been reported," Layne said. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
